---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import FIRECalculatorBase from '../../components/calculator/FIRECalculatorBase.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Lean FIRE Calculator — Calculate Your Minimalist Early Retirement Number"
  description="Free Lean FIRE calculator to plan minimalist early retirement. Calculate your FIRE number using the 25x rule with conservative 20x multiplier. Instant results with interactive charts."
  canonical="https://truefinancetools.com/lean-fire-calculator"
  ogImage="https://truefinancetools.com/og-lean-fire-calculator.png"
  ogImageAlt="Lean FIRE Calculator - Plan Your Minimalist Early Retirement"
  pageType="article"
  keywords="lean fire calculator, lean fire number, minimalist retirement, early retirement calculator, fire calculator 20x, lean fire strategy"
>
    <FIRECalculatorBase fireType="lean" />

    <section class="border-t border-hairline bg-canvas-soft py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-center text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          What is Lean FIRE?
        </h2>

        <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none text-body">
          <p class="mb-4">
            <strong>Lean FIRE</strong> is a minimalist approach to early retirement that requires just <strong>20x your annual expenses</strong> saved. It's designed for people who are comfortable living on less — digital nomads, minimalists, or those in low cost-of-living areas.
          </p>

          <p class="mb-4">
            Unlike Regular FIRE (25x) or Fat FIRE (30x), Lean FIRE prioritizes time freedom over lifestyle spending. The trade-off is clear: you can retire years earlier, but you'll need to maintain a leaner budget in retirement.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">The Lean FIRE Formula</h3>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-canvas-soft-2 p-4 font-mono text-sm text-ink">
            Lean FIRE Number = Annual Expenses × 20
          </div>

          <p class="mb-4">
            For example, if you spend $40,000 per year, your Lean FIRE number is $800,000. That's $200,000 less than Regular FIRE ($1,000,000) for the same expenses.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Who Should Choose Lean FIRE?</h3>
          <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Digital Nomads</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">Location-independent workers who can live affordably in low-cost countries while traveling the world.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Minimalists</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">People who find happiness in experiences rather than possessions and naturally spend less.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Early Savers</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">Those who want to retire as quickly as possible and are willing to make lifestyle trade-offs.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Low COL Areas</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">People living in areas with affordable housing, healthcare, and daily expenses.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-hairline bg-canvas py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 text-center sm:px-6">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          Explore Other FIRE Strategies
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-8 text-body">Compare different approaches to find the right one for your lifestyle.</p>

        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
          <a href="/fat-fire-calculator" class="group rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-5 text-left shadow-sm transition-all hover:shadow-md">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink group-hover:text-link">Fat FIRE Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-body">For those who want a luxury retirement lifestyle.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/coast-fire-calculator" class="group rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-5 text-left shadow-sm transition-all hover:shadow-md">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink group-hover:text-link">Coast FIRE Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-body">Let compound interest do the heavy lifting.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/barista-fire-calculator" class="group rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-5 text-left shadow-sm transition-all hover:shadow-md">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink group-hover:text-link">Barista FIRE Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-body">Work part-time, let investments cover the rest.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
</PageLayout>
